8.3.22  9:56 am   how come you spelled nobody as "knowbody" at first in the video?

      "no" and "know" sound the same. and they both appear in that line. so i couldn't resist the opportunity to swap them briefly, especially because 'knows' created an entirely alternate word ('nose'). also under the veil of pixelation i thought it was appropriate to do more mischievous things

8.3.22  9:39 am   do you think we have free will?

     yes

      even if we don't, does that actually matter, so long as we feel as if we do?

     i personally don't think we would even perceive the conscious experience if we did not have access to a certain extra dimensional layer of wiggle room (i.e. the opportunity to select or even change the immediate future). i believe if it were 100% deterministic and pre-determined, i don't think we would ever be aware of our existence at all, and time would already be done
